8922	[The sections functor is corepresented by \(j_!\mathcal{O}_V\)]
8923	  \label{lem:sectionsFunctorCorepIso}
8924	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.sectionsFunctorCorepIso}
8925	  \uses{lem:jshriek_corepr, lem:sectionsFunctor_additive}
8926	  For an open \(V \subseteq X\) there is a natural isomorphism of additive functors
8927	  \[
8928	    \operatorname{sectionsFunctor} V
8929	      \;\cong\;
8930	    \operatorname{Hom}_{X.\mathrm{Modules}}\bigl(j_!\mathcal{O}_V,\, -\bigr)
8931	  \]
8932	  between \(\Gamma(V, -)\) and the covariant additive hom-functor corepresented by
8933	  \(j_!\mathcal{O}_V\). It is the functorial upgrade of the corepresentability bijection of
8934	  Lemma~\ref{lem:jshriek_corepr}.
8935	\end{lemma}
8936	\begin{proof}
8937	  \uses{lem:jshriek_corepr, lem:sectionsFunctor_additive}
8938	  Assemble the natural transformation from the additive corepresentability isomorphism
8939	  \(\operatorname{Hom}(j_!\mathcal{O}_V, \mathcal{F}) \cong \Gamma(V, \mathcal{F})\) of
8940	  Lemma~\ref{lem:jshriek_corepr}, taken componentwise; its naturality square in \(\mathcal{F}\) is
8941	  exactly the naturality of that bijection in the coefficient sheaf. The components are
8942	  isomorphisms, so the assembled transformation is a natural isomorphism. Both functors are
8943	  additive (Lemma~\ref{lem:sectionsFunctor_additive} and the additivity of a hom-functor).
8944	\end{proof}
